{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Programs · OIATC{% endblock %}
{% block description %}OIATC runs four programs that put Indigenous-led digital governance into use: Anishinaabemowin, Anokii, community knowledge, and member resources. Each has shipped work and a clear funding ask.{% endblock %}
{% block og_title %}OIATC programs{% endblock %}
{% block og_description %}Four programs that put Indigenous-led digital governance into use, each with shipped work and a clear funding ask: language, sovereign infrastructure, community knowledge, member resources.{% endblock %}
{% block body_class %}route-programs{% endblock %}

{% block head_styles %}{% include 'partials/funder-styles.html.twig' %}{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
<article class="fund-wrap">

  <p class="fund-eyebrow">OIATC</p>
  <h1>Four programs. One premise.</h1>
  <p class="fund-lede">The systems meant to serve First Nations are rarely chosen by them. Each program puts that right in a different place. All four have shipped work, and each page says what the next dollar unlocks.</p>

  <div class="fund-cards" style="margin-top: var(--gap-6)">
    <article class="fund-card fund-card--flag">
      <div class="fund-card__k"><span>Language · Flagship</span><span class="fund-card__badge">live</span></div>
      <h3><a href="/programs/anishinaabemowin">Anishinaabemowin</a></h3>
      <p>Language revitalization with consent infrastructure. A fluent Elder's corpus, a lesson app, learning games, the talking doll, and story nights, all on technology the community controls.</p>
      <a class="fund-card__unlock" href="/programs/anishinaabemowin">What is shipped, and what funding unlocks &rarr;</a>
    </article>
    <article class="fund-card">
      <div class="fund-card__k"><span>Infrastructure</span></div>
      <h3><a href="/programs/anokii">Anokii</a></h3>
      <p>Nation-governed community platforms built on Waaseyaa. Two community vantages are live today, with a regional coverage plan from Sault Ste. Marie to Sudbury to Manitoulin ready to fund.</p>
      <a class="fund-card__unlock" href="/programs/anokii">The live vantages and the rollout plan &rarr;</a>
    </article>
    <article class="fund-card">
      <div class="fund-card__k"><span>Knowledge</span></div>
      <h3><a href="/programs/community-knowledge">Community knowledge</a></h3>
      <p>Plain-language explainers members actually use: treaty annuities, the Massey solar project, where community data lives, and responsible AI in coursework. One has already been cited by local press.</p>
      <a class="fund-card__unlock" href="/programs/community-knowledge">The explainers and their reach &rarr;</a>
    </article>
    <article class="fund-card">
      <div class="fund-card__k"><span>Transparency</span></div>
      <h3><a href="/programs/transparency">Member resources</a></h3>
      <p>Helping members use their right to see how their governments and systems work: organization explainers, records requests, and responsible disclosure, done with documentation discipline.</p>
      <a class="fund-card__unlock" href="/programs/transparency">What you can ask for, and how &rarr;</a>
    </article>
  </div>

  <section class="fund-sec">
    <div class="fund-statement">
      <p>When communities choose and govern their digital systems, the systems fit. When the systems fit, services and language outcomes improve. We exist to make the first part true.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="fund-more">
    <p class="fund-more__k">More</p>
    <div class="fund-more__links">
      <a href="/about">About OIATC</a>
      <a href="/support">Support and partner</a>
      <a href="/news">News</a>
    </div>
  </div>

</article>
{% endblock %}
